gurmukhi: ਸਭੈ ਦੇਵ ਥਾਪੇ ਕੀਯੋ ਦੁਸਟ ਨਾਸੰ || ਟਰੇ ਸਰਬ ਦਾਨੋ ਭਰੇ ਜੀਵ ਤ੍ਰਾਸੰ ||੫੩||
transliteration: Sabhai Dev Thaape Keeyo Doust Naasan|| Dare Sarab Daano Bhare Jeev Traasan||53||
translation: After destroying the tyrants, the Lord established again all the gods, and demons frightening the creatures were destroyed.53.

gurmukhi: ਸੰਖਾਸੁਰ ਮਾਰੇ ਬੇਦ ੳੁਧਾਰੇ ਸਤ੍ਰੁ ਸੰਘਾਰੇ ਜਸੁ ਲੀਨੋ ||
transliteration: Sankhaasur Mdare Bed Udhdare Satru Sanhdare Jas(u) Leeno||
translation: The Lord received great approbation of killing the demon Shankhasura, redeeming the Vedas and destroying the enemies.

gurmukhi: ਦੇਵੇ ਸੁ ਬੁਲਾਯੋ ਰਾਜ ਬਿਠਾਯੋ ਛਤ੍ਰ ਫਿਰਾਯੋ ਸੁਖ ਦੀਨੋ ||
transliteration: Deve Su Bulaayo Raaj Bithaayo Chhattra Phiraayo Soukh Deeno||
translation: He called Indra, the king of gods and blessed him with royalty and its comforts.

gurmukhi: ਕੋਟੰ ਬਜ ਬਾਜੇ ਸੁਰ ਸਭ ਗਾਜੇ ਸੁੰਭ ਘਰਿ ਸਾਜੇ ਸੋਕ ਹਰੇ ||
transliteration: Kotan Baj Baaje Sur Sabh Gade Sounbh Ghar(i) Saaje Sok Dare||
translation: Millions of musical instruments began to resound, the gods began to play th tune of bliss and the sorrows of every house were destroyed.

gurmukhi: ਦੈ ਕੋਟਕ ਦਛਨਾ ਕ੍ਰੋਰ ਪ੍ਰਦਛਨਾ ਅਾਨਿ ਸੁ ਮੱਛ ਕੇ ਪਾੲਿ ਪਰੇ ||੫੪||
transliteration: Dai Kotak Dachhnaa Kror Pradachhnaa Aan(i) Su Machchh Ke Paae Dare||54||
translation: All the gods bowed in respect at the feet of Fish incarnation presenting various types of gifts and making millions of circumambulations.54.

gurmukhi: ੲਿਤਿ ਸ੍ਰੀ ਬਚਿਤ੍ਰ ਨਾਟਕੇ ਗ੍ਰੰਥੇ ਪ੍ਰਥਮ ਮੱਛ ਅੳੁਤਾਰ ਸੰਖਾਸੁਰ ਸਮਾਪਤਮ ਸਤੁ ਸੁਭਮ ਸਤੁ ||੧||
transliteration: It(i) Sribachitra Naatake Granthe Pratham Machchh Aoutaar Sankhaasur Samaptam Sat(u) Soubham Sat(u)||1||
translation: End of the description of the first Machh (fish) Incarnation and Killing of Shankhasura in BACHITTAR NATAK.
Now begins the description of Kachh (Tortoise) Incarnation:

gurmukhi: ਕਿਤੋ ਕਾਲ ਬੀਤਯੋ ਕਰਯੋ ਦੇਵ ਰਾਜੰ || ਭਰੇ ਰਾਜ ਧਾਮੰ ਸੁਭੰ ਸਰਬ ਸਾਜੰ ||
transliteration: Kito Kaal Beetyo Daryo Dev Raajan|| Bhare Raaj Dhaamannd Soubhan Sarab Saajan||
translation: Indra, the king of gods, ruled for a long time and his palaces were full of all materials of comfort;

gurmukhi: ਗਜੰ ਬਾਜ ਬੀਣੰ ਬਿਨਾ ਰਤਨ ਭੂਪੰ || ਕਰਯੋ ਬਿਸਨ ਬੀਚਾਰ ਚਿੱਤੰ ਅਨੂਪੰ ||੧||
transliteration: Gadan Baaj Binan Binaa Ratan Bhoopan|| Daryo Bisan Beechaar Chittan Anoopan||1||
translation: But once Vishnu reflected upon a unique idea in his mind that this king is without elephants, horses and jewels (therefore something should be done in this direction).1.

gurmukhi: ਸਭੈ ਦੇਵ ੲੇਕਤ੍ਰ ਕੀਨੇ ਪੁਰਿੰਦ੍ਰੰ || ਸਸੰ ਸੂਰਜੰ ਅਾਦਿ ਲੈ ਕੇ ੳੁਪਿੰਦ੍ਰੰ ||
transliteration: Sabhai Dev Ekatra Keene Purindran|| Sasan Soorajan Aadh Lai Ke Oupindran||
translation: Indra gathered together all the gods including Chandra. Surya and Upendra.
